<item>
 <title>The Ultimate Alba Playlist</title>
 <link>https://trobar-test.sites.stanford.edu/ultimate-alba-playlist</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Statement of intent:  I tried to transcribe with contemporary songs the tension contained in the genre of the alba: the longing, the timeless parenthesis and the parting; the strong delimitation between the night world and the day world, the triangular structure between the lovers and the gaita, the illegitimacy of the lover&amp;#039;s true love and their opposition to society. I chose popular songs because the melodies of the albas were known by the audience (to the extent that a religious song could be a contrafactum of an erotic alba) and alos because the refrain is the most important rethorical element of the genre, and comes again and again as a cyclic utterance, a fatal warning. I created the playlist on a music sharing platform because it seemed appropriate for a genre that circulated from one court to another, and from one country to another. Here is the playlist and some comments on the choice of the songs. 1.J-Lo-Waiting for tonight (represents the longing for the upcoming night, like in the genre of the serena, which is a reversed alba); 2-The Doors-Moonlight Drive (represents the timeless pleasure of the lovers protected by the night); 3-Akon-Nobody wanna see us together (when dawn comes, the illegitimacy of the lovers&amp;#039; true love is revealed); 4-Shaggy-It wasn&amp;#039;t me (classic adultery song with the intersting presence of a third character giving advice to the lover, reminds us of the antithetic structure: lovers and gaita against the gilos); 5-Dawn (Go Away) (a personification of Dawn to underline its allegorical power); 6-The Eagles-Tequila Sunrise (shows the strong melancholy that seizes the lovers that have to part from each other); 7-Phil Collins-Against All Odds (illustrates the physical tear caused by the separation, illustrates the lament dimension of the genre); 8-The Beatles-Good morning (ultimately shows how daylife ironically starts anew, with all its social constraints and hypocrisy). Enjoy!&lt;br /&gt;
